ov, C. Van Hulse, P. Vanhoefer, G. Varner, K. E. Varvell, A. Vinokurova, V.\n  Vorobyev, M. N. Wagner, C. H. Wang, M.-Z. Wang, P. Wang, X. L. Wang, M.\n  Watanabe, Y. Watanabe, S. Wehle, K. M. Williams, E. Won, Y. Yamashita, S.\n  Yashchenko, Y. Yusa, Z. P. Zhang, V. Zhilich, and A. Zupanc","title":"Search for $B^+ \\to e^+ \\nu$ and $B^+ \\to \\mu^+ \\nu$ decays using\n  hadronic tagging","comments":"13 pages, 7 figures, Submitted to PRD","journal-ref":"Phys. Rev. D 91, 052016 (2015)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevD.91.052016","report-no":"Belle Preprint 2014-8, KEK Preprint 2014-2","categories":"hep-ex","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We present a search for the rare leptonic decays $B^+ \\to e^+ \\nu_e$ and $B^+\n\\to \\mu^+ \\nu_\\mu$, using the full $\\Upsilon(4S)$ data sample of $772\\times\n10^6$ $B\\bar{B}$ pairs collected with the Belle detector at the\n$\\small\\textbf{KEKB}$ asymmetric-energy $e^+ e^-$ collider. One of the $B$\nmesons from the $\\Upsilon(4S) \\to B\\bar{B}$ decay is fully reconstructed in a\nhadronic mode, while the recoiling side is analyzed for the signal decay. We\nfind no evidence of a signal in any of the decay modes. Upper limits of the\ncorresponding branching fractions are determined as ${\\cal B}(B^+ \\to e^+\n\\nu_e)<3.5\\times 10^{-6}$ and ${\\cal B}(B^+ \\to \\mu^+ \\nu_\\mu)<2.7 \\times\n10^{-6}$ at 90$\\%$ confidence level.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 24 Jun 2014 19:55:44 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 30 Dec 2014 03:14:18 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 5 Mar 2015 06:19:36 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 25 Mar 2015 06:51:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-03-26"}
