{"id":"1406.6594","submitter":"Dietmar Weinmann","authors":"Dietmar Weinmann, S. N. Evangelou","title":"Parity-dependent localization in $N$ strongly coupled chains","comments":"9 pages, 5 figures","journal-ref":"Phys. Rev. B 90, 155411 (2014)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevB.90.155411","report-no":null,"categories":"cond-mat.dis-nn cond-mat.mes-hall","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Anderson localization of wave-functions at zero energy in quasi-1D systems of\n$N$ disordered chains with inter-chain coupling $t$ is examined. Localization\nbecomes weaker than for the 1D disordered chain ($t=0$) when $t$ is smaller\nthan the longitudinal hopping $t'=1$, and localization becomes usually much\nstronger when $t\\gg t'$. This is not so for all $N$. We find \"immunity\" to\nstrong localization for open (periodic) lateral boundary conditions when $N$ is\nodd (a multiple of four), with localization that is weaker than for $t=0$ and\nrather insensitive to $t$ when $t \\gg t'$. The peculiar $N$-dependence and a\ncritical scaling with $N$ is explained by a perturbative treatment in $t'/t$,\nand the correspondence to a weakly disordered effective chain is shown. Our\nresults could be relevant for experimental studies of localization in photonic\nwaveguide arrays.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 25 Jun 2014 14:51:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-10-09"}
